        <mxCell id="16" parent="15" style="shape=note2;boundedLbl=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;size=15;verticalAlign=top;align=left;" value="Architectural and Technical Decisions:&lt;div&gt;1. Apply two type of memory:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;- a. Short-term memory: memory type conversation memory to summerize when context too long, Thread-scoped, use langgraph checkpoint checkpoint.&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;- b. Long-term memory: Vector Strore Memory,&amp;nbsp;Semantic search over past conversations.&lt;br&gt;2. Checkpointer strategy:&amp;nbsp;LangGraph&#39;s built-in MongoDBSaver checkpointer with pros like native integration and auto-serialization. Therefore, introduce NEW collection dedicated for this purpose.&lt;br&gt;3. Thread ID mapping: using session_id map to LangGraph&#39;s thread_id&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;- introduce new collection called &quot;conversation&quot; and map 1-1 to session..&lt;br&gt;4. Memory scopes and limits:&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;- Support full history (keep all messages), this simplest way but could cause hit limits in long conversation. This need to have memory summary mechanism during long conversation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
